						<summary>

						<p>States that general <hi rend="bold">Pedaya</hi> and a certain <hi rend="bold">Maṁchi</hi> gave gifts of perpetual lamps to god Prasanna Kēśava of Kōlavennu and that the former gave a piece of land to <hi rend="bold">Kāṭe Bōyuṇḍu</hi> on condition of his paying 24 <hi rend="italic">Gōkana-rūkas</hi> (coins) annually for the upkeep of his lamp.</p>						

